CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 2, 1957, page 19, reads: "The Mayor Spoke... at a Citizens for Lawrence luncheon Monday at Hotel Webster Hall. Seated at the speaker's table, left to right: Richard B. Tucker Jr., the Rev. Hugh S. Clark, Mayor David L. Lawrence, Philip Baskin, and John McKee. - 'Teenie' Harris Photo."David L. Lawrence was Mayor of the City of Pittsburgh 1946-1959, Governor of Pennsylvania 1959-1963, and he died in 1966.
TitMainTitle: Group portrait including, from left to right, Richard B. Tucker Jr., Rev. Hugh S. Clark, Pittsburgh Mayor David L. Lawrence, Philip Baskin, and John McKee, seated at speakers banquet table at the Citizens for Lawrence luncheon in Hotel Webster Hall
